reviews: The room is to smal for two persons. We did not have space at all och hardly place for luggage. Breakfast was average, lack of plate and bowls, limited number. eggs only in one form. too little fruit and green.

Loved our stay -would come back. The room was small and tight but great shower and confortable bed. Loved the food options. Staff very friendly. Cool lighting in room and the tablet control panel for the room was great. One point off because it was tight for two and no where to really sit except small desk chair and on the bed which was against two walls so had to be climbed into. However the many comforts meant we would be back!

Great location, steps away from metro stations and its right on champs elysees! Great cafes and restaurants are a few min walk. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Lives up to CitizenM motto of luxury that doesn't break the bank!

Very nice staff, attentive and friendly, the hotel is clean, confortable and has a nice decoration also has great location with many attractions around the food is acceptable but also there are other restaurants, the rooftop bar has a nice view…Definitely I will go back.

The best location you could ask for , at a very decent price as with all citizenm hotels i have been on staff are just the best
Rooms very clean small for 2 great for 1
Brilliant colours
They have a wondefful rooftop bar with great food and drinks and a crazy view
. As always breckfast not good but coffee not bad will come back

Amazing and modern customer experience to stay at this Citizen M hotel. Ad libitum drinking water to take to room, life of school books to read in all rooms, staff were uniquely friendly, in room tablet to manage light/tone and cleaning - and if you decline daily cleaning some days of own choice - the hotel will donate to people in need.

In addition, great location - nice garden - great rooftop - lobby with friendly atmosphere.

Everything about the hotel was awesome,the only problem I had was with the size of the room.art work was beautiful,modern technology in the room,lovely staff always eager to help with a smile on their face.

The most unprofessional hotel that I have ever booked. I booked this hotel for 6 nights stay in Paris. I rang reservation to leave a note for my arrival time.
The person who responded was so unprofessional, rude and unfriendly that made me think I should cancel the trip and stay elsewhere.
If you try to contact the hotel directly, you'll find that there is no way you can contact them - there is not phone, email or other ways to contact unless you ring up their general directory number.

Loved the clean modern room, the huge bed, the tech in the room that actually made everything easy (instead of adding unnecessary complications), the friendly staff and last but not least, the amazing location at the center of Champs-Elysee.

I’ve stayed at CitizenM Boston, Los Angeles and Shoreditch. I’ve loved all of them. I’ve always had amazing service at the bar and restaurant. This location is very understaffed. I do not recommend. I received raw pizza and they refused to refund. They also didn’t have anyone to serve drinks. The waitress/bartender is checking in guests and only one person. This is a very disappointing CitizenM.

The Hotel has the best Location, room are so clean (Little small but is ok) and the staff are so friendly, the breakfast was good, the rooftop was nice, Definitely I will stay again in my next trip to Paris!

Staff were helpful and so friendly! Absolutely AMAZING location! So close to so many restaurants and shopping stores. You can even walk to Arc de Triomphe from here as well. Rooms are clean and consistent amongst all CitizenM hotels. Can’t beat this place. Forever a fan of CitizenM Hotels.

The entire purpose of my 48 hours in Paris was to shop as this was not my first visit to Paris. This location was perfect as I could walk to the stores and the Metro 1 stop was one block away. Check in was seamless and the Ambassadors were nice and helpful. The decor, and layout of the hotel is phenomenal. Room was small but it was to be expected in Paris. The use of the space in the room was great. I loved controlling everything with the IPad which is provided in the room. Room was very clean and bed was comfy! My only issue was the the US outlet didn’t work. Fortunately I had a universal adapter. I also felt the entryway was sort of dark at night but I experienced no issues.

The hotel is very nice and its location is great. But the room service is ZERO. They don’t clean the room, the maximum they do is to change the towels.
We stayed for 6 nights, and they didn’t even change the bedsheets.
The bus station is in front of the hotel, and the metro station is minutes away.

CitizenM Champs Elysees is a great location for those who want to visit Paris either as a tourist or for business purpose. Super central. Modern comfort with great lounge areas and a nice rooftop overlooking the Tour Eiffel! My new favorite hotel in Paris.

10/10 if it were an option. The location is outstanding. We walked to the Louvre, Arch, Eiffel and more on some days and took metro others. Restaurants right there as well as shopping. There’s a small grocery store outside for snacks and water and 2 metro stations + bus steps from hotel. Hotel is very clean and super fun. Staff spoke English if you need this. Roof top bar has view of Eiffel Tower and nice drinks. Would 100% stay again and look into locations elsewhere as well.

Very nice hotel, on a perfect location!!! The rooms are quite small, but clean and enough for a few nights. The staff are very friendly. The room is equipped with a tablet for operating the room appliances such as the tv and the curtains! Very convenient!

Amazing stay. After reading some reviews was concerned about room size but when arrived there is nothing to be worried. Good size bedroom. Huge bed and shower cubicle. Clean and fresh bedding and towels. The staff members were all friendly and smiling. The hotel is in a great location. Food served 24/7 and tasty food. The only think I would point negative is no USB plug in bedrooms, as so modern and technological hotel that was expected.

Stayed at CitizenM Paris this past weekend. I am quite disappointed in the quality of accommodations that I received. It’s a shame as the team are incredibly nice and it’s a quaint little hotel in a fantastic location.

However, I was there for one night for an important work trip so a good night's sleep was the primary focus of my stay. The room was frankly pretty cold the moment I stepped in, but at around 11pm in the evening it started to become freezing with a severe draft permeating from the window. I tried to sleep but just found it impossible as it was so cold - I think this hotel is cutting the hours of heating or something, because the room warmed up all of a sudden at 6am and I was able to get 3 hours of sleep. Not good.

Also, the shower was lukewarm at best, so I just skipped out on that and waited until I got to the airport lounge the next day, to have one.

Usually love CitizenM hotels and have stayed in the ones in NYC before, however, this one sadly really did not met my expectations. Above all, the most important part of a hotel stay is the quality of the sleep you are able to get. After my one night stay, I woke up the next day feeling chilly and exhausted before a very important meeting.

Good location, super service, affordable price. Room is small but very functional for small group size. It has everything we asked for during a 6-day stay at Paris. Convenient to public transportation.

CitizenM Champs Elysées is located right at the shopping heart of Paris. The rooms as small but efficient, ultra modern and the bed is AMAZING (best night of sleep you'll ever have)! Very friendly and helpful staff, though most don't speak French.

Affordable hotel with a great location. I’d definitely return. Room was small but still nice. I didn’t need a big luxurious space since we were out sightseeing most of the time so this was perfect. Rooftop bar was amazing. The technology in the room was also very impressive. I’d definitely return.

Quality of the hotel is incredible. Rooms are super clean, staff and the hotel itself are very welcoming and cool to be in/with, tech that really works (from iPad controlling lights and AC, to the app on your phone, to the TV with Chromecast and Apple TV, making it extremely easy to relax with your content). Stayed before, decided to repeat the experience and will probably do it again in my next visit to Paris.

Being able to buy late check-out on the app, on my own, without needing to check availability with staff was great. I feel so independent when I'm using any service of CitizenM. It's a freedom I wish I had everywhere.

CitizenM = No headaches!

Nice stuff and recepcion. But the rooms were so small and complexe. Couldnt turn off the AC. The Lights and be curtins were dificult to manage. In four days nobody cleaned the room. But the worse to us Was the fact that they dont accept any payment in cash.

The friendliest, most exceptional staff I have ever encountered in 25 years of traveling around the world! They truly went above and beyond and made an experience that could have been an utter disaster, one of the most memorable of my life! We will always have a special place in our hearts for the staff of CitizenM

Wonderful location, amazing service, value for money.... nothing was to hard, would highly recommend to anyone. Rooms a touch small and beds a bit awkward but you make it work as there was adequate storage space, nooks and crannies for storage...... amazing views of Paris and room top lounge... totally wonderful staff and experience...... loved it!!

The travel service we booked through added on a $39 breakfast that we did not request. The ambassordors told us we had to go back to the travel service for a refund. We requested a van at 6:40 am to take us to the airport. It never came. They were scrambling to find the reseveration and then just booked a new one (I was standing right there and could see what they were doing) telling us 'it's on it's way'. A car that was too small showed up. Miraculously, a van showed up for another fare that declined so we were able to use it.

Menu and A/C experience could be improved, possibility to switch off fully A/C and to order in with the ipad would be fantastic.
Amazing decoration in the shared areas.
Smart rooms are very fun and exciting.

I was in Paris for two days with work and needed a confortable place to stay/work/eat.
The staff in citizenM Paris Champs-Elysees were really exceptional, always helpful with a positivity that really stood out. Great vibes and fantastic coffee!
My room was a decent size and was calm, even though it was facing the Champs-Elysees.
I'll certainly book here again!

What a place, location and concept this is! Friendly staff that make you feel like you're at home. Overal design all over the hotel is very cool and inspiring. Great value and what a view from the CloudM!
I will definitely be back again soon.

Thanks again Citizens !!

Recent visit, awesome room, great location, best hotel staff ever. Rooms are clean, breakfast amazing. Hassle free, rooms high tech everything controlled by i pad. Steps away from champs elysee, but the staff is the best!!!!

Wonderful location. I was traveling solo in business. Would also be great for young couples.

Breakfast was tasty - coffee and espresso was perfect. Nothing like having drinks on a rooftop bar looking at the Eiffel Tower.

Would not be good for families.

An extremely outstanding hotel with the most amazing ambassadors.
We were treated like royalty throughout our entire stay.
Excellent location for all the designer shops and attractions.
We can't wait to return and we actually had tears in our eyes when we had to leave.
We would super highly recommend to anyone.
The happy memories will stay in our hearts for ever.

Brought my best friend for some retail therapy, food and drinks and it did not disappoint. Super friendly staff, really cool hotel with quirky little touches and when we came back very drunk the team took care of our well being and looks after us we will definitely be returning! Thank you so much Amy & Kerry x

I love Citizen M, I love the style and the design of accommodation. Hotel staff is always nice and friendly: most of activities could be done autonomously by Citizens, anyway the Steffens is always there smiling and happy to support.
It’s really affordable luxury.

One night stay in Paris. Cozy room, really nice location and breakfast is amazing. The bed are really comfortable, I was able to sleep without hearing any noise coming from outside (which is exceptional in Paris!).

Really great hotel with wonderful common spaces, great breakfast and clean and comfortable rooms. Ideally though rooms would be a little bigger. Staff extremely friendly and helpful, you feel like at home with friends

This hotel is full of Art - from the lobby to the corridors. It was a new experience for me to self check-in / check out , control the room light , mood , air-conditioning ,curtains and blinds all from your phone . It from the IPad already waiting for you in the room.
The room was very pleasant although small , but cozy and clean .Breakfast was excellent and varied. The hotel team was very friendly, patient and helpful.
Very much enjoyed our stay.

Where do I start? The hotel is very well located, the common areas are cozy and trendy, the ambassadors very friendly and attentive, the room layout is perfect and there is room for everything. I loved the security of the property, and I just wish I could’ve stayed longer!!

Stylish, unique and great employees and service. Very good breakfast, great technology, the iron heaven its literally heaven grat iron machine. The service is amazing I slept very good. The automatic blind curtains was a nice touch

Nice hotel concept at perfect solution. Exceptional service, compact but comfortable room, super breakfast, try coissant and scrambled eggs with salmon, fast check-in and check-out. Make sure that you are able to use iPad and have credit card.

Superb location
Literally Steps away from the champs elysees and a one minute walk to the Metro (subway)

Unbelievably amazing staff
Specifically Omar , Zac and Louie were fabulously kind and went out of there way to help us !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

we have just returned from spending 3 nights at CitizenM Champs Elysees and we loved it. It is a brilliant hotel and I would highly recommend it to other young people. It is very hip, cool and modern. I felt like the culture in the hotel was great, the staff were friendly and helpful, and I felt there was a good vibe.
I personally enjoyed the room, it was super clean and the bed was made up fresh every day! based on other tripadvisor reviews I had read before arriving I expected the room to be tiny, however I found the room to be a fine size for 2 people, the storage is compact but there is a little space for everything (shelves, a desk, a small wardrobe, a sideboard by the bed, a mini fridge under the sink, a safe stored somewhere reasonable) and it provided what you need, the lighting and the television are controlled by the iPad which was fun, I especially liked the different mood lighting in the shower and the different AM & PM shower gel, plus the nice soap by the sink for hand washing.
I will now make a point of looking for CitizenM Hotels when I travel to different cities, our only real negative concern was the hotel bar not accepting cash, we would really liked to have spent more time in the hotel bar to enjoy their cocktails but due to it being digital-only we ended up going elsewhere, as cash was our means of spending on our trip.

This hotel was booked based on the positive reviews on Trip advisor. The location of the hote is amazing, it’s like Oxford street of London. Reception staff are very polite and helpful. There are lots of places to eat and drink around the hotel. The reception is located on the second floor. The use of black colour everywhere gives the unknown claustrophobic feeing.
***The service to clean the rooms is poor***
I has water leaking in the walking shower and despite having requested for room service my room was not cleaned until my return and repeated request at 4 pm when I came and called the reception. I was told the housekeeping service is going around to getting to my place. Personally I feel they forgot, which is fair enough. I specifically told the housekeeper that my room has sand and water in various places which needed attention, and showed the areas of concern but all that meant nothing. She simply made my made with sand gave new towels and that’s it. There is no point of room service if you are not going to clean despite being told what the mess is.
The breakfast is priced at 16.95 euro per person per day which I found slightly costly for what they offer. For hot breakfast It was potatoes,scrambled eggs and bacon. Cold breakfast was 3 types of Musli,yogurt, 1 type of cheese and fruit salad, usual juice and coffee.
To be honest being considered 4 star I was not impressed overall. The mattress is also very soft and bouncy which did not help trying to get good night sleep. The pillow was very comfortable.
Also the room we stayed was away from Main Street side and there was no sound at all which is positive stuff.
Would I return to the same hotel I would say maybe not because I am sure for the price paid I can get a better quality of stay at another 4 star hotel or find a cheaper hotel for the same level of service.
Would I recommend this hotel - based on reception staff politeness and location yes.

a very cool, artistic, practical hotel at a very good location right in the center of champs Elysees.
the hotel has several seating areas, suitable for couples and businesses.
Although the variety of food at the breakfast is limited, everything served is of high quality.
the staff are extremely kind and helpful, so it seems like a good workplace too.
the rooms are extremely clean and comfortable

The hotel location is amazing, service amazing, people are great. The rooms are just too tight you don’t have a place to open your suitcase . The outside area in lobby level is so much fun. Staff ultra friendly

Another great location for Citizen M. I’ve stayed at their London hotels many times and this one just off the Champs Élysées has the same high standards. A few tech problems but the staff were absolutely superb from reception to the bar and canteen.

Wonderful, lively, colorful, surprising, modern, great friendly staff.
I was taken aback a little when I entered the hotel, the fact that the "reception" was at the second floor and that I had to go through some technological device.... Then the enticing reference to be a citizen of the hotel, was somehow playing a funny role, though you are in a hotel, the feeling is to be in a space that feels more like university friends' apartment than a hotel. The setting is great, colorful, new fruniture, clean, great people, good breakfast, great position.

Poor standard. Unfortunately ruined our trip, when we arrived our room was ready, when we did get our room we feel like the cleaning was very rushed or not done at all, dirty, found human hair in our bed and around the floor in bathroom, stained toilet bowl of which looks like to be sick. Stay away

Great location. Great Value for money. Fast check in and out. Safety was a priority and they didn’t disappoint. Lounge was clean and roomy. Rooms had everything you’ll need. Location was exceptional. Friendly staff.

As everyone else states, the rooms are tiny, almost dormlike. Traveled with my wife, ended up staying here as many reviewers commented on the rooftop bar and 2nd floor outdoor space as well as your not in the room all that much. Stayed 3 nights, which was too long in this small of a room. Showering/getting ready to go out, etc became a challenge with just my wife and I. First night it was kinda cute, 2nd night ok, and by the 3rd, became a little tiresome. Everything else, service, staff, location, etc are great. The bed was comfortable, it was just too small of a room with little storage/place to put luggage or clothes.

very convenient and easy trip including successful hotel choice. The location is marvelous achieved all of my business needs and family shopping requirements. If I am going to visit Paris again which in the near future ! definitely I will choose the same hotel I stayed IN this time.

We would highly recommend staying at citizenM Paris Champs-Elysees! The location is right around the corner from the Champs-Elysees; however, the hotel was extremely quiet for the entire week we were there. We loved the staff, and felt like our business was appreciated. They were very pleasant and approachable whenever we had questions. As far as the room, it was quite small, but we really only slept there so that was not a negative at all. Most importantly, the bed was extremely comfortable and it was fun being able to operate the electrical system with the i-Pad!

Loved the tech, friendly staff, great overall decor. Room was barely big enough for 1 person, but had to put my suitcase on the bed, no rack or place to put it. Recommend, but ask about room size if >1 person.

I loved this hotel! Superb location right in Champs Elysee. The hotel is very modern, nicely decorated, with a rooftop with a view of Effeil Tour! Staff is very friendly. Cafeteria 24 hours. Rooms are very comfortable, HOWEVER, very small! If you have a large suitcase, this hotel is not for you. If you have two small suitcases you will also have problems! The rooms are only 14mts. For that, I found the hotel quite expensive.

Amazing location. Great room - remember they are small but perfect. Very clean great breakfast. Brilliant staff and the location is really amazing. Rooms are app controlled and the check in and check out was so easy.

Checking in is extremely easy, stuff is amazing, do you speak various languages. Location is extremely convenient, I cannot emphasize this more it’s location it’s fantastic. You can walk from there to many places and you have a subway station within five minute walk. I will definitely go back on stay at the CitizenM

This was our second stay at a CitizenM hotel and the first at the hotel Champs Elysées. Fantastic experience from check in to check out. Location was perfect and had easy access to the metro system allowing us to tour parts of the city that were a little too far on foot. Staff were really friendly and had great local knowledge when it came to places to eat/drink and visit.

The roof top terrace is definitely worth a visit as it has a nice view over looking part of the Champs Elysées and the Eiffel Tower which of an evening is great to sit back and enjoy a few drinks from.

Having stayed in the the New York CitizenM, the fantastic experience at this hotel was exactly the same if not better. Id highly recommend this hotel for either business or pleasure visits.

The CitizenM is a great location on the Champs-Elysees. The staff were very friendly and it was very clean. Please note: the rooms are very tiny but they make up for it in all of the public spaces. I would definitely recommend this hotel for a single person or a couple. No more than 2 people to a room.

Our second trip to this great hotel! Really friendly and helpful staff. Lovely and clean, and the food and drink was great too. The terrace is a really nice spot to take a moment with a coffee. Looking forward to returning!

This is a great place, great location, great people and very clean. Please note: the rooms are very very tiny. Just understand this when booking so you are not surprised. The cleanliness, staff and public spaces all make up for the small rooms. Say hello to Zac from Alabama. :-)

The staff is unbelievably helpful, friendly and nice! the hotel is like home you do not want to leave even in Paris and food was surprisingly yummy! Thank you to the CitizenM team - Can't wait to come back!

I really enjoyed my stay with my cousin at this hotel, a modern and beautifully designed hotel with friendly staff.
The lobby, the furniture, the accessories, the colorful ambiance, make this hotel really special.
It really worth the price, the rooms are small but comfortable and clean and cosy.
Definitely will come back everytime I want to stay in paris.
The location, the design, cleanliness, staff and service all great!
Thank you citizenm!
It was a pleasure 😊

Excellent location, walking distance to cafes and high end stores. Walk friendly location. Very clean rooms, well maintained and friendly/professional staff. Layout and design of the room is perfect for travelling couples.

City center not to far off the beaten path conveniently located near metro stations, shopping and fine dining!!! It was an absolute splendid experience that I would recommend to all my family and friends. The staff is above professional and friendly, they will absolutely treat you with dignity and respect! 10/10 recommend again and again and again!!

This was my first time staying at a citizenM hotel and I absolutely loved it! The vibe is so modern, chic and I love how the lobby looks like a living room. The breakfast is delicious, as are the drinks but it's really the staff that makes the hotel stand out. I can't say enough good things about how we were treated on this trip. Nelle and Mahendiran, big shout out to you for being so nice, accommodating and fun! Def will come back when I'm in Paris again soon.

It was a perfect experience to stay at this hotel for four nights. The staffs were very kind and friendly, and is was a family atmosphere. The room is comfortable and effectively structured, and the food of the breakfast was very good. I would like to recommend to any traveler to stay at this hotel and I will absolutely use this hotel when I come again in Paris.

I was a few days with my daughter in Paris. The location of the hotel is perfect, just a few steps near the Champs Elysees. Clean rooms and very friendly staff. Food is good, nice drinks.
Would recommend the hotel.

Great location, great service, affordable, friendly ambassadors fantastic stay, right next to the metro and centrally located to walk to a number of sites, with the added advantage of shopping on one of the best streets in Paris. Great view of the Eiffel Tower too from the roof top terrace. Had the best iced coffee in Paris!!

excellent hotel right in the heart of paris. Easy to get around, walking and they were great when we needed a cab with the system that they have at the hotel.
We knew the rooms were small but they are extremely efficient as we knew we would be there to mainly sleep, We had small carry on luggage which was fine, but it we had big suit cases it may have been too tight

Love the quirkiness and individuality of Citizen M hotels. Tour de France final weekend, the city was buzzing and CloudM rooftop bar gave us a great view of the proceedings. Staff are so friendly and helpful, really do make your stay special.

Stayed here for one night on business, and was so impressed. Great bedrooms, very helpful and friendly staff and the design in the hotel is so quirky and cool. I would highly recommend the CitizenM, certainly a brand I will look out for.

I have had my share of drab cookie-cutter hotel rooms where I am treated like a number and worse. This experience changed everything for me. I am a fan forever. I was respected, cared for and the room was superb. I slept like a baby and that is saying something because I very rarely sleep in hotel rooms.

Love the tech and efficiency of this hotel, and in a great location. Pizza was not bad, rooftop bar was really enjoyable. Staff is extremely friendly and helpful, even though most things are automated. The app is the best I've seen with all the functionality it has.

You cannot turn off the A/C in the rooms and the rooms are so small - the rooms are not really ideal for a family trip, mostly for couples or for 1 person travel. The location is great and so is the breakfast. Service is the best.

A great hotel in the heart of the 8th district. Rooms are rather small with very little storage space, but otherwise good and comfy and loaded with gadgets. Breakfast is good and the common areas are delightful...feels like home.

Great location. Staff are very friendly, professional and helpful!
Room is nice, clean and cozy and the bed is very comfortable.
The lobby has multiple indoor and outdoor areas filled with comfortable chairs and tables to enjoy.

The hotel was in an excellent location. Walking distance for shopping, Uber and taxi accessible. Excellent restaurants around the area. Monoprix in front where you can get essentials. Rooms very high tech iPad controlled everything. Lobby was great. Also upstairs had area where you can actually see the Eiffel Tower.
If not for the fact that I got double charged for the room I would rate this hotel 5 star.
I booked everything via Expedia and the hotel incorrectly charged my credit card again. When I contacted Expedia the hotel did a refund but maybe because of the currency exchange the refund was less 25 dollars. So I essentially lost 25 dollars because of their mistake. Trying to contact my bank but this is wasting too much of my time cause now my bank is asking for more information. It’s only 25 dollars but it’s the principle of losing money without receiving any service or goods.
Beware of the taxi they use too. Even though it is supposed to be flat rate of 53 euros to go to the airport the driver asked for 59 euros. I did not even bother arguing.
Aside from the fiasco of the double hotel charge it could have been a very excellent stay.

Excellent service, nice F&B and outstanding breakfast & bar offerings. Rooms are very small which was disappointing but you can always come down to the lobby to do your extra work. Check-in and Check-out is super high-tech as they have self processing machines ready on the spot!

Very nice hotel. Tiny rooms (as I find in most European hotels.) The room was overly techy, and it just made for unnecessary complication and a TV that did not work for our entire stay. The location is perfect for the Metro, food, shopping, sights.

Best hotel I’ve stayed in for a long long time. Staff were so helpful and friendly, room was spotless, and really useful interactive interface with the app letting you control lighting, climate, blinds etc completely remotely. Fantastic view of the Eiffel Tower from the rooftop terrace, ideal location just off Champs Elysees, 5 min walk from two Metro stations. Would definitely stay here again, and look forward to trying out some of the other CitizenM hotels out there!

Nice location! Very small room lacking adequate storage. Nice shower. Mostly helpful, pleasant staff. However, was asked to leave the lobby area because I had a Starbucks drink I purchased outside. In all my years of world travel I’ve never been asked to leave a lobby because I hadn’t purchased my coffee at the hotel. Disappointed!!

My BFF and I have been planning a trip to Paris since 2019...Then Covid happened, and finally! We made it! We went for a morning walk through the city and bought some coffee. When we arrived back to Citizen M we sat in the lobby to plan our day. A hotel employee asked us to leave the lobby because we did not purchase our coffee from the hotel. My friend and I waited for three years, flew 7 and 1/2 hours from the States, paid for 8 nights at this hotel, and could not sit in the lobby because we brought our coffee in from our morning walk. Generally, the staff seem nice, the room is fine, but this ruined it for me.

Great location and service. Definitely recommend it. Close walking distance to everything. Clean rooms, delicious food, friendly staff and convenient location. Will visit again if we go to Paris. Love it.

Trendy hotel in the heart of the Champs-Élysées with wonderful staff. Outstanding shower. Lovely rooftop. Very cramped room overall, however, and we had the largest room in the hotel. I had to work during my stay and the room simply wasn’t big enough. The bed was tucked into an alcove such that it was only accessible from one side. If there are two of you, one has to crawl over the other. Closet space was so minimal as to be nearly nonexistent. I would not stay here again.

I highly recommend this hotel. Staff is super friendly and helpful. the beds are big for European standards and rooms are extremely clean. location is amazing! steps from champs-elysees, restaurants, bars, stores. pharmacy. so worth it.

We selected this hotel due to its location not knowing what to expect. Wow. Our overall experience was amazing. The "Ambassadors" (how they refer to their staff) were super friendly, accommodating, and so nice to talk with. The facilities were exceptionally clean, comfortable, and carefully thought out. We normally stay at the big luxury chains, but our experience with CitizenM has changed our way of thinking. The concept is great starting with the non-reception area to the living rooms and various areas for lounging and relaxing. The food and coffee were great. The entire atmosphere was such that we felt at home and enjoyed engaged conversations with the Ambassadors. It feels like we made new friends. Finally the hotel is good value for your money. They have certainly converted us. I highly recommend this hotel chain if you have an opportunity to discover it for yourself.

We booked this hotel in Paris because of the location and online pictures. citizenM exceeded our expectations! The location was perfect and from the moment we walked in, the staff were helpful and attentive. The hotel had a wonderful vibe and public areas were decorated with fun and interesting art and furniture. There are two outdoor spaces that we enjoyed after our days of sightseeing. If you want a fun friendly hotel in Paris at a great price, this is it. it also happens to be in great location with many attractions in walking distance.

Having looked at a number of hotels for Paris we settled on this one, predominately for the location.
The location is superb but the hotel was also first class. It’s very modern, everything in the room is done via an iPad. Room was fairly small, but taking into account the location and cost was absolutely fine. Very clean and fresh.
Staff were helpful and although it’s designed to be fairly autonomous (you check yourself in for example) they were always around when needed.
The rooftop bar became a regular top before and after dinner as the views were great and very peaceful considering the location.
Would happily stay in a CitizenM again.

The hotel is beautiful, contemporary, fun. The location is exceptional right on the corner of Champs Elysee, next to Tiffany. The beds are heaven and the shower is luxurious. That said, it is the staff that is this hotel’s secret sauce. Each and every team member is warm, friendly, knowledgeable and goes the extra mile to make sure guests get their needs met. I am a general manager for luxury brands, and the level of service at this hotel rivals the best.
Thank you for a lovely stay.

The bathroom in the bedroom could have more privacy and the hours of use of the restaurant and rooftop spaces should not be limited in time. The decor is amazing and the location is exceptional, as is the view from the rooftop!

No stuffiness here. friendly, modern and efficient hotel. Rest and reenergize in your soundproof room. Situated close to 2 subway stations with great sites to visit in walking distance. Wide choice of restaurants close by.

Great place to fill luxury but not snobby.
Modern Art makes the place surprisingly cozy.
The phylosophy of online app works perfetly on the room and also for check-in and check-out.
Personal has no problem with anything also, so there was no problem at all, all the time.

The hotel is located centrally in Champs elysees and, opposite the hotel is Gallery La Fayette. It is a beautiful hotel. When you check in, the lounge is really impressive and the decor is just amazing. Staff is friendly and check in was smooth.
We love our stay here. Room is a tad small but who is complaining….bed is super comfortable and the room is clean.
The ambient lighting is such a welcome at night and in the room has an iPad that controls everything.
We love the hotel and we have nothing to complain about. The roof top bar is amazing with views to the Eiffel Tower.
I highly recommend this place if you are looking for a hotel that is centrally located, great staff, great food and a super comfy bed to rest after exploring Paris. The terrace is such a bonus for you to sit outside and have a few drinks.
We will come back without any hesitation…..and we will be back.

Location- 10 (for touristic visit)
Service - 10 (even more), always yes, always help, always smile and kind
Design- 10- like a modern art museum- you have always interesting stuff to see, nice rooftop balcony with the Eiffel view, and garden balconies as well.
The room is modern and not as small as you’d expect in Paris center.
Bottom line- if you need a central hotel, don’t hesitate to come here.

AMAZING staff and fantastic location. Rooms are not big but are exactly what you need (who does anything but sleep in there anyways??). I have never found rooms with bigger than double beds before so having a King size here was luxiourious. Will try to stay here on all future trips to Paris.

Arrived the hotel on 9am, a super friendly girl called Cheryl let me check in immediately when we arrive, although the check in time suppose to be 2pm.
The hotel is very modern and new! Managed to get high floor room so the view is nice! Definetely will be back again! Thanks Cheryl!

room was rather small but extremely modern and clean. the bar experience was great however at the rooftop bar we couldnt get drinks and they sent us down to the other bar. location is great just around the corner at champs elysée

Top and central accommodation, stylish envirnonment, everything is perfect and well done. If you want to be close to the main stops, do it and enjoy everything. Roof top bar is amazing with the right view.

Never in my life I have experience such a small room in a hotel. !!!
About the size of a closet. Beware come with a small bag that you can shove in a drawer under the bed
For 350 euros a night with no breakfast !!!
The bed is comfortable the shower is good but for the rest it is a disgrace
The staff is friendly but not very efficient
The top was when 6 of us were having drinks on the roof top terrasse at 6pm. I wanted an expresso as well as my drink
I was told in a rather severe manner that I had to go and drink it on the 2nd floor. And if I got it there I could NOT bring it to the 8th floor terrasse I had to drink it by the reception and then return to the 8th floor.
If you can, stay away from this hotel.
It is a major rip-off. There are so many good hotels for that price in Paris.
